    <p>WASH­ING­TON • Air pol­lu­tion killed 476,000 new­borns last year, with the big­gest hot spots in In­dia and sub-Sa­ha­ran Africa, ac­cord­ing to a new global study.</p>
    <p>More than 116,000 In­dian in­fants died from air pol­lu­tion in the first month of life and the fig­ure was 236,000 in sub-Sa­ha­ran Africa, ac­cord­ing to the State of Global Air 2020.</p>


